==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released post The Falcon and The Winter Soldier. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|You were a super soldier, like [[Steve Rogers|Steve]].|[[Sam Wilson]] to Isaiah Bradley|Truth}}
*'''Artificially Enhanced Physiology''': In an attempt to recreate [[Project Rebirth]], Bradley, and many other black American soldiers, were subjected to torture and experiments with the [[Super Soldier Serum]]. This serum proved to be a success on Bradley, who developed similar abilities to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]. However, the program was eventually buried under the rug.
**'''Enhanced Strength''': [[File:IBradley-FlyingBag.png|thumb|250px|Bradley punches a bag far away]]As a super soldier, Bradley possesses increased strength. Even in his advanced age, he was able to fling a metal can with enough force to embed it within a wall. He can also carry his heavy objects such as potted plants with no difficulty, and in his prime, he was able to remove the [[Winter Soldier]]'s [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|titanium arm]]. Whilst training with Sam, Bradley was able to launch a punching bag several meters away with his punches and kick, as well as swing it around like a melee weapon.
**'''Enhanced Durability''': Bradley’s bones and muscles are very durable, this allowed him to survive and disarm [[Winter Soldier]] in combat, as well as survive injuries that should be fatal. Even whilst brainwashed in the White House, Isaiah was able to jump out of a window and safely land outside.
**'''Enhanced Speed''': Due to the [[Super Soldier Serum]], Bradley possesses enhanced speed; during his brainwashed assassination in the White House, he managed to successfully flee, outrunning many soldiers, until he regained cognisance  at a nearby park.
**'''Enhanced Agility''': Bradley's agility was also increased, allowing him to make swift and quick movements. Whilst brainwashed, Bradley was able to temporarily evade capture, and deftly leap out of a window.
**'''Enhanced Stamina''': Bradley's stamina was heightened, allowing him to take on the mission of saving his fellow super soldiers. Despite his senior age, whilst brainwashed, Bradley attempted to assassinate the U.S. president, then escaped from the White House and temporarily evade capture.
**'''Enhanced Reflexes''': In addition to agility and speed, Bradley could move and react more quickly; enabling him to dodge objects and attacks.
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': Bradley could heal from injuries very quickly, enabling him to get back to battle with minimal recovery time.
**'''Longevity''': As a result of the [[Super Soldier Serum]], Bradley ages much slower than the normal human, a trait he shares with fellow super soldiers [[Steve Rogers]] and [[Bucky Barnes]]. Despite having been a young adult in the [[1950s]] and living up to [[2024]] without being placed in cryostasis, he has the bearing of a man a few decades younger.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released post The Falcon and The Winter Soldier. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|I took half that [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|metal arm]] in that fight in [[Goyang]].|Isaiah Bradley to [[Sam Wilson]]|The Star-Spangled Man}}
*'''Expert Combatant''': As a former soldier, Bradley is trained in hand-to-hand combat. During the {{WPS|Korean War}}, he was able to overpower [[Winter Soldier]] and rip his metal arm off.
*'''Expert Tactician''': Bradley has a very calculating mind, he alone managed to save countless prisoners from concentration camps.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Bradley Residence]]''': Isaiah Bradley lived in this house with [[Eli Bradley]] following his release from prison. This is where he was when [[Sam Wilson]] and [[Bucky Barnes]] met with him to discuss his past as a super soldier.

